readme:
# Atom Cobalt Material Syntax A dark blue theme that takes the classic Cobalt and Material themes and smashes them together. Inspired by Silvestre Herrera's [Atom Material Syntax](https://atom.io/themes/atom-material-syntax).
![screenshot](https://i.imgur.com/8PZEnLo.png?1)
Also check out [Atom Minimal UI](https://atom.io/themes/atom-minimal-ui) for a user interface that works beautifully with most syntax themes. ### Installation From the command line: `apm install atom-cobalt-material-syntax` Or directly in Atom: 1. Open __Settings__ > __Install__ 2. Set the filter to __Themes__ 3. Search for `atom-cobalt-material-syntax` and click __Install__ ### Note In some atom grammars for [R](https://cran.r-project.org/), notably [language-r](https://atom.io/packages/language-r), >= is not recognised as a single comparison operator. The solution is to use [atom-language-r](https://atom.io/packages/atom-language-r).
